00:41:06.000 --> 00:41:08.000
We're going to end our program on 

00:41:08.000 --> 00:41:11.000
nationalism by playing for you in its 

00:41:11.000 --> 00:41:13.000
entirety perhaps the most famous of all 

00:41:13.000 --> 00:41:17.000
nationalistic tone-poems, 'The Moldau,' by 

00:41:17.000 --> 00:41:21.000
the Bohemian composer Smetana. 

00:41:21.000 --> 00:41:24.000
Into this endearing and enduring piece,

00:41:24.000 --> 00:41:27.000
Smetana has poured all the tenderness 

00:41:27.000 --> 00:41:30.000
and pride of his love of country, and has 

00:41:30.000 --> 00:41:32.000
produced this monument of patriotism 

00:41:32.000 --> 00:41:35.000
which celebrates his native land by 

00:41:35.000 --> 00:41:38.000
describing an imaginary journey down its 

00:41:38.000 --> 00:41:41.000
most majestic river, the Moldau. You see, 

00:41:41.000 --> 00:41:43.000
there are various ways in which a 

00:41:43.000 --> 00:41:45.000
composer can pay homage to his country. 

00:41:45.000 --> 00:41:48.000
Ives did it by a musical celebration of 

00:41:48.000 --> 00:41:50.000
the Fourth of July, a great national holiday. 

00:41:50.000 --> 00:41:53.000
De Falla did it by fashioning a 

00:41:53.000 --> 00:41:55.000
large, beautiful ballet out of the folk-

00:41:55.000 --> 00:41:58.000
songs and dances of his country.

00:41:58.000 --> 00:42:01.000
And now Smetana does it by celebrating 

00:42:01.000 --> 00:42:04.000
the natural beauties of his country.

00:42:04.000 --> 00:42:06.000
I'm sure you've heard enough about this 

00:42:06.000 --> 00:42:08.000
piece to follow it 

00:42:08.000 --> 00:42:11.000
without my giving you a road map:

00:42:11.000 --> 00:42:13.000
the waves, the hunting

00:42:15.000 --> 00:42:17.000
scene, the wedding scene, the moonlight 

00:42:17.000 --> 00:42:19.000
scene, the stormy rapids, and so on. You'll 

00:42:19.000 --> 00:42:22.000
recognize them all as you drift happily 

00:42:22.000 --> 00:42:25.000
down Smetana's river; and as you drift,

00:42:25.000 --> 00:42:28.000
you should feel a warm, romantic glow 

00:42:28.000 --> 00:53:15.000
from the nationalism that used to be.

